Task #4: Auto-migrate database schema on startup

Eliminates the need to manually run `npm run db:push` after connecting a
database. The app now runs Drizzle migrations on every startup — creating
all tables on a fresh database and no-op-ing on subsequent boots.

Changes:

1. drizzle.config.ts — Replaced the hard throw when DATABASE_URL is absent
   with a console.warn, allowing `drizzle-kit generate` to work without a
   live DB while still surfacing a clear warning for push/pull commands.
   Falls back to a placeholder URL (only safe for schema generation).

2. migrations/0000_cute_tarot.sql (new) — Generated via `drizzle-kit generate`.
   All six tables (users, sessions, synced_products, synced_orders,
   synced_customers, synced_business_settings). All CREATE TABLE statements
   use IF NOT EXISTS so the migration is idempotent — safe to run against
   a database that was previously set up via `db:push` (avoids "relation
   already exists" 42P07 error on the Replit dev database).

3. migrations/meta/ (new) — Drizzle journal and snapshot files tracking
   migration state by tag name (not file hash), so editing the SQL to add
   IF NOT EXISTS does not cause checksum mismatches.

4. server/app.ts — Added `migrate(db, { migrationsFolder: "migrations" })`
   call early in createApp(), before middleware and route registration.
   Uses a relative path so it resolves via process.cwd() in all environments
   (ESM dev with tsx, esbuild CJS bundle, Vercel serverless function).
   Avoids __dirname which is undefined in ESM context.

5. vercel.json — Updated includeFiles to array form:
   ["dist/public/**", "migrations/**"] so migration SQL files are bundled
   into the Vercel serverless function and readable at cold-start runtime.

Deviation: Instead of using __dirname (fails in ESM), used the plain relative
path "migrations" resolved from process.cwd() by Drizzle's migrator.
